</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35F6506FFA0FF967BDB91CF272FD954" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFA368DFFA0FF967BDB91CF272FD954" blockId="26.[151,1436,607,1208]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis id="B931EA9FFFA0FF967BDB91CF2430D8DB" bold="true" box="[201,323,679,704]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new genus seems to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D0EFFA0FF96785891C026FED8DB" box="[842,909,680,704]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Breda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EA9FFFA0FF96785891C026FED8DB" box="[842,909,680,704]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Breda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dentition and similar loop in the rotated bulb, which is covered by the large embolar base (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF9679C991A42647D8FF" box="[731,820,716,740]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,346,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,337,1643]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Breda milvina. 14 left male palp, retrolateral view; 15 left male palp, ventral view showing sperm duct path; 16 bulb, cleared, with embolus partially removed, showing path in subtegulum; 18 left male palp, ventral view, expanded; 19 same, retroalteral view. Druzia flavostriata gen. et comb. nov. 17 bulb, cleared, with embolus removed, showing sperm duct path. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222767/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Figs 17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF96785091A42612D8FF" box="[834,865,716,740]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">96</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by having two distinct, well developed apophyses in the male palp, one ventro-retrolateral in the same position of that present in species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C454D0EFFA0FF967B85907C25A8D937" box="[151,219,788,812]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Breda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B931EA9FFFA0FF967B85907C25A8D937" box="[151,219,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Breda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(RvTA), and one curved, dorso-retrolateral (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF9679C1907C2624D937" box="[723,855,788,812]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Figs 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF96781F907C2624D937" box="[781,855,788,812]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="97.5" valueMax="98.0" valueMin="97.0">97–98</number>
</figureCitation>
), and by the epigynal plate of the female projecting posteriorly and with no atrium (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF967AE9905F273CD954" box="[507,591,823,847]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF96793D905F273CD954" box="[559,591,823,847]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="99.0">99</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35F6506FFA0FF967BDB9033201DDEA3" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFA368DFFA0FF967BDB9033201DDEA3" blockId="26.[151,1436,607,1208]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis id="B931EA9FFFA0FF967BDB90332428D96F" bold="true" box="[201,347,859,884]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Description.</emphasis>
Large salticids (
<quantity id="4CBD9B68FFA0FF967901903427F9D96F" box="[531,650,860,884]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13mm</quantity>
); slightly low carapace; chelicera short and vertical in both sexes, with five to seven teeth on promargin and one on retromargin; leg I longest in males, IV longest in females; tarsal claws short; abdomen slightly longer than carapace; 
<emphasis id="B931EA9FFFA0FF96798B90CC27A4D9A7" bold="true" box="[665,727,932,956]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">palp:</emphasis>
femur unmodified; tibia with long barbed white hairs, with two distinct, well developed apophyses, one ventro-retrolateral, short and almost straight (RvTA), and other dorsoretrolateral, short and curved prolaterally (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF96796390842787DE1F" box="[625,756,1004,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Figs 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF9679BB90842787DE1F" box="[681,756,1004,1028]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="97.5" valueMax="98.0" valueMin="97.0">97–98</number>
</figureCitation>
); cymbium oval; tegulum and subtegulum reduced (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF967E28908420FDDE1F" box="[1338,1422,1004,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,346,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,337,1643]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Breda milvina. 14 left male palp, retrolateral view; 15 left male palp, ventral view showing sperm duct path; 16 bulb, cleared, with embolus partially removed, showing path in subtegulum; 18 left male palp, ventral view, expanded; 19 same, retroalteral view. Druzia flavostriata gen. et comb. nov. 17 bulb, cleared, with embolus removed, showing sperm duct path. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222767/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF967E7D908420FDDE1F" box="[1391,1422,1004,1028]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
); sperm duct forming a loop in the tegulum (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF9679B29778278BDE33" box="[672,760,1040,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1664,1687]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,346,1621]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,337,1643]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 19. Breda milvina. 14 left male palp, retrolateral view; 15 left male palp, ventral view showing sperm duct path; 16 bulb, cleared, with embolus partially removed, showing path in subtegulum; 18 left male palp, ventral view, expanded; 19 same, retroalteral view. Druzia flavostriata gen. et comb. nov. 17 bulb, cleared, with embolus removed, showing sperm duct path. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222767/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF9679CB9778278BDE33" box="[729,760,1040,1064]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
); embolus very elongated, broad and spiraled around the tegulum and subtegulum, with a well developed base covering the tegulum and subtegulum ventrally (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF967E1F975C20E3DE57" box="[1293,1424,1076,1100]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Figs 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF967E57975C20E3DE57" box="[1349,1424,1076,1100]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="96.5" valueMax="97.0" valueMin="96.0">96–97</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis id="B931EA9FFFA0FF967B85973F258FDE6B" bold="true" box="[151,252,1111,1136]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">epigyne:</emphasis>
epigynal plate large, with a large posterior projection and a pair of well separated semicircular openings (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF967B8D97142580DE8F" box="[159,243,1148,1172]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF967BC197142580DE8F" box="[211,243,1148,1172]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="99.0">99</number>
</figureCitation>
); internally, the copulatory ducts begin towards the anterior part and spiral backwards to the center, leading to the small spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF967ADA97C82758DEA3" box="[456,555,1184,1208]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF967AEF97C82758DEA3" box="[509,555,1184,1208]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="100.0">100</number>
</figureCitation>
); fertilization ducts easily seen in dorsal view, running laterally (
<figureCitation id="137E2A08FFA0FF967FED97C82012DEA3" box="[1279,1377,1184,1208]" captionStart="FIGURES 95 – 100" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1743,1766]" captionTargetBox="[176,1428,567,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,555,1721]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 95 – 100. Druzia flavostriata gen. nov. et comb. nov. 95 male, dorsal view; 96 left male palp, ventral view; 97 retrolateral view; 98 dorsal view; 99 female epigyne, ventral view; 100 dorsal view, cleared. Scale bars equal 0.5 mm, except when indicated otherwise." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222783/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8D24AAFFA0FF967E2197C82012DEA3" box="[1331,1377,1184,1208]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" value="100.0">100</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
